				<td colspan="2"><span>If they eliminate all methods of Bard solo ability, they're gonna end up eliminating alot of bards.
<br />

<br />
That'd basically be a fatal mistake, since it causes 2 major problems.
<br />

<br />
One Problem is they cannot afford to tune encounters expecting that ZERO bards will be present.  Because then if you have one, it can significantly effect the encounter.
<br />

<br />
Second problem is, they could not afford to tune encounters REQUIRING a bard to be present, if they go and wipe the population out of bards, then guilds will bitch to all holy h*ll that there are no bards and they can't do anything without them.  Sorta like the cleric requirement/shortage problem.
<br />

<br />
They would have to re-tune so many encounters or suffer major player losses.</span></td>
